Hi,

This is to suggest a modification of the JIRA REST-API to permit synchronizing fields that are not on the JIRA create screen from an outside source. We have raised a question already ("JIRA Rest API forces fields to be on Create-Screen to sync using ConnectALL" https://answers.atlassian.com/questions/33158217/jira-rest-api-forces-fields-to-be-on-create-screen-to-sync-using-connectall), however the REST-API doesn't support this service. I also came across a related issue reported here ("JIRA REST 5.0 - Create Issue Error" https://answers.atlassian.com/questions/48192/jira-rest-5.0---create-issue-error), so it seems we're not alone with this desire.

We're using Go2Group's ConnectALL to sync issues in JIRA with requirements in HP QC. Certain fields are not included in the create screen of JIRA due to restrictions made by our JIRA administrators that cannot be canceled. However, we need to transfer fields from HP QC to JIRA that are not on the JIRA create screen and we cannot so because the REST-API doesn't support this. Placing those fields on the create screen and hinding them from the user through scripts is also no option because the use of such scripts is not supported within our organization. In my oppinion the limitation of the REST-API to fields that are only on the create screen impairs the benefit of an automated data exchange between connected systems.

